import 'dart:io';

/// Loads the contents of a fixture file from the `test/fixtures/` directory.
///
/// This is a utility function for testing purposes, allowing you to
/// easily read mock JSON or other static files used in unit and
/// integration tests.
///
/// ## Parameters
/// - [name] â†’ The name of the fixture file (e.g., `"user.json"`).
///
/// ## Returns
/// The contents of the file as a [String].
///
/// ## Example
/// ```dart
/// final jsonString = fixture('user.json');
/// final userMap = jsonDecode(jsonString);
/// ```
///
/// ## Notes
/// - The path `test/fixtures/` is relative to the root of the project.
/// - Throws [FileSystemException] if the file does not exist or cannot be read.
String fixture(String name) => File('test/fixtures/$name').readAsStringSync();
